rComments: Dasha's great, very relaxed in class and makes it easy to speak. The exams are fair.

Love her! Great teacher and very reasonable. The coursework load was average: homework every day but it wasn't demanding or incomprehensible. Friendly and approachable, enjoys her job (I imagine...) Class is an easy A as well. Has a good sense of humor too.
She's a very wonderful instructor. Don't stop at the second level, Dasha is a fantastic instructor. :)
Dasha's really cool. She assigns a lot of bookwork but she seems mostly interested in what you're learning. Pretty laid back about in-class work as well.

Dasha is really cool and is a lot of fun. She assigns a lot of bookwork to do, but it's mostly really easy. She's very easy to contact and get ahold of and she's willing to help you if you need it. The only thing is that for a third year Russian class, I wish it were more immersion based. I think more would get done that way. Exams are reasonable.
